00:32:13,100 --> 00:32:14,100
This is it?

498
00:32:14,100 --> 00:32:17,700
This cable carries a live feed into the
stock exchange building next door.

499
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:19,800
??? There was a fault in the system

500
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:23,800
and George was sent over from the company
in Houston who supplied the software.

501
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:26,700
His team had to dig up the cable

502
00:32:26,700 --> 00:32:29,700
so that they could fit a new
digital transcoder unit.

503
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:34,200
When we did, I realised with an
exposed cable and the right software,

504
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:36,600
we could manipulate the data
that passes through it.

505
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,500
This is a hard drive.

506
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:40,400
It records all of the data coming in

507
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:43,800
and holds it up for nine tenths of a second
before playing it on down the line.

508
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:46,600
- To the stock exchange?
- Exactly.

509
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:48,900
It holds it up long enough
for us to analyse it

510
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:52,400
and identify any major shifts,
trends or movements,

511
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:55,200
before playing it on to the
stock exchange boards.

512
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,200
It's also hooked up to
our trading account,

513
00:32:57,200 --> 00:33:00,300
so it can make purchases
based on those calculations.

514
00:33:00,300 --> 00:33:03,100
Wait. You're saying you
can analyse the data

515
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:07,100
and actually purchase stocks before
the stock exchange gets the same information?

516
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,900
That's exactly what I'm saying.

517
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:10,900
But that's, that's genius.

518
00:33:10,900 --> 00:33:12,400
Can this be done?

519
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:15,300
Well, if,
if what they're saying is true.

520
00:33:15,300 --> 00:33:19,000
- It's absolutely true.
- And there's no risk. Ever.

521
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,100
We only ever buy stock
we know is going to rise.

522
00:33:21,100 --> 00:33:24,700
And presumably you can off-load before
anyone else if it starts to go down?

523
00:33:24,700 --> 00:33:27,700
We don't hold on to it that long, we
just make our profits and get out.

524
00:33:32,500 --> 00:33:35,400
OK, I'm in.

525
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:37,000
You're in?
In for what?

526
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,600
You will make investments for me.

527
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:41,300
Look, I'm sorry,
it's not that simple.

528
00:33:41,300 --> 00:33:43,300
I heard you in the restaurant.

529
00:33:43,300 --> 00:33:45,700
You said you have a
capacity for ten million.

530
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:49,600
Well, yes, I mean, that's the top
end of our buying power but...

531
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,800
But what?

532
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:53,000
Well, even if we had
that kind of money,

533
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
which, by the way, we don't,
we'd never go over a million,

534
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,400
we don't want to draw
attention to ourselves.

535
00:33:57,400 --> 00:34:00,000
That's because you're a horse's ass.

536
00:34:01,100 --> 00:34:05,000
You will invest the full ten million.

537
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:08,600
- Ten million?
- Hedge fund managers invest hundreds of millions in a day,

538
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:10,400
why would anyone notice ten?

539
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:14,400
Because we're private brokers
trading for private investors.

540
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:17,200
Then you buy the stock in my name,

541
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:21,800
no-one will question that level
of investment if it's from me.

542
00:34:22,300 --> 00:34:25,300
You take my ten million,
you double it.

543
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:27,200
Look, well I'd need all
the money in the account.

544
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:29,600
- And the returns?
- They'd go to the same account.

545
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:32,900
Miss Hammond will put
everything in place.

546
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:36,100
Look, I don't know, we'd have to
programme in a new trading account,

547
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:39,300
- and re-set the buying criteria.
- Then do it.

548
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:42,200
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
what do we get out of this, huh?

549
00:34:42,200 --> 00:34:45,200
Yeah, I mean we still
get our commission, right?

550
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:47,400
Er, 22%. Cash.

551
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,600
- Five per cent.
- What?

552
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,700
Perhaps the experience will
teach you some manners.

553
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:56,900
You call me when it's ready.

554
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:05,200
OK, once the money is
in the trading account,

555
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:08,000
I want two men watching
Cole around the clock.

556
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,200
Yes, sir.

557
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:12,500
I want you to learn how
they programme the machine.

558
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,300
Me? Why?

559
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:17,700
Because once you can use it,

560
00:35:17,700 --> 00:35:20,600
I'll have no further use for Cole
and the old man.

561
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:22,800
Wait.

562
00:35:25,100 --> 00:35:27,400
I don't mind bending the
rules to make money,

563
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:30,000
the City's corrupt anyway.

564
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,700
But I won't be a party to murder.

565
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,300
Would you rather 
I asked someone else?

566
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:41,100
Cos then, I wouldn't need you either.

567
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:44,600
No.

568
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,300
Then just do it.

569
00:35:47,900 --> 00:35:49,900
Call my enforcer,
get him on a plane.

570
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:08,100
OK, time to bail out.

571
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:11,700
- You what?
- He wants me to learn how to programme the machine.

572
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:13,800
So that he can have you killed.

573
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:16,400
Well, that's kind of
what we expected.

574
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:19,300
He told Barir to call the
enforcer and whatever you do,

575
00:36:19,300 --> 00:36:21,400
he's not going to let you
out of his sight.

576
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:23,100
I know.

577
00:36:23,100 --> 00:36:26,600
From tomorrow morning he'll have
two of his guards on you full time.

578
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:29,600
Even if you pull this off,
you'll never get away clean.

579
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:32,000
This is wicked.

580
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:34,700
Without a doubt, this is one of the
coolest things I've ever tried on.

581
00:36:34,700 --> 00:36:37,500
I actually look like I could
swim faster than a shark!

582
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,500
- All right, Stace?
- Hi.

583
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:42,100
Just for the record,

584
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:45,500
this isn't an accurate
representation of my underwear.

585
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,400
Pleased to hear it.

586
00:36:50,900 --> 00:36:53,300
He's got issues, from
when he was a baby.

587
00:36:53,300 --> 00:36:55,300
I do not have issues.

588
00:36:56,400 --> 00:37:00,100
Mickey, I don't like it.

589
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:04,000
- It feels wrong.
- What about the money?

590
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:07,700
He's having it transferred first thing
tomorrow before the markets open.

591
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:11,600
He's also bringing 500,000
in cash which is your commission

592
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:14,900
- if you double him up.
- OK.

593
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:19,100
I tell you someone's planning to have
you killed and all you say is OK?

594
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:23,300
You're taking ten million
from this man, Mickey,

595
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:26,700
