there's nothing to keep him here,

624
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:03,800
where as we, on the other hand,

625
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:06,700
will cash in and be long gone

626
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:08,700
by the time the dust settles.

627
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,900
It will work.
Trust me.

628
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,800
Hello.

629
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:27,700
We have a job.

630
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:31,300
Stay in your room,
I will send over a package.

631
00:39:44,100 --> 00:39:45,800
- You OK?
- Yeah.

632
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:53,900
So, it must be nice
to see Stacie again.

633
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:57,200
- Yeah, yeah, it is.
- Yeah, Ash told me that you two, um,

634
00:39:57,400 --> 00:40:00,300
- you were quite close for a while.
- Yeah, we were.

635
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:03,500
- Yeah, you go back a long way.
- Yeah, that's right.

636
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:10,100
So, this, er, whole break thing.

637
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:13,600
You know the whole, um,
going our own way thing.

638
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:17,700
Only it's a bit sudden
and it's a bit like,

639
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:21,600
Stacie turning up the way she has
and I just, I...I was wondering

640
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:23,400
if the two things were
related in any way.

641
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:27,200
It's just curiosity, really,
It's a good job I'm not a cat.

642
00:40:27,300 --> 00:40:30,100
- No, the thing, the thing is...
- No, it's not.

643
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:32,300
- It's not what?
- Related.

644
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:34,500
OK.

645
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:38,100
It's just... I want to live
a normal life for a while.

646
00:40:38,900 --> 00:40:40,800
Get to know people
for who they are.

647
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:45,700
Not constantly look at them and see
if they'd make a great mark or not.

648
00:40:46,100 --> 00:40:48,100
So, it's more like a holiday, really?

649
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:51,000
- Yeah, I guess so.
- Yeah, so we could still, you know, like,

650
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:54,400
meet up and spend time together
and...and chill.

651
00:40:55,700 --> 00:40:56,800
I'd like that.

652
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,300
Me too.

653
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:01,100
 Then the work thing wouldn't
be there any more, would it?

654
00:41:01,100 --> 00:41:02,100
No, it wouldn't.

655
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:07,600
And if everything goes right tomorrow,
then you know, we'll be stinking rich.

656
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,900
Yes, we will.

657
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:12,600
So, at some point,
we could be talking

658
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:16,600
you and me, and a desert island and,

659
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:19,800
like, a couple of million
in the bank or something.

660
00:41:22,500 --> 00:41:24,200
That doesn't sound
too shabby, does it?

661
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:26,200
No, it doesn't.

662
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:32,200
OK, good.

663
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:38,000
Great, well, then I'll just
leave you to your thinking.

664
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,400
I just thought I'd ask.

665
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:43,900
I'm really glad you did.

666
00:42:15,900 --> 00:42:19,500
OK, so you go when Albert calls
Nick to give him the thumbs up.

667
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:21,500
Hard and fast, OK?
Lots of noise.

668
00:42:21,500 --> 00:42:24,400
We need them scared enough
to run straight to the airport.

669
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:27,400
Everyone in cuffs and
dragged out to the vans.

670
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:30,600
So, we're going to be outside
the London Stock Exchange, in broad daylight,

671
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:32,700
so it won't be
long before the real old bill notice.

672
00:42:32,700 --> 00:42:35,500
So, don't hang about, get them
in the vans and on your way.

673
00:42:35,700 --> 00:42:38,000
The mark is last up.

674
00:42:38,300 --> 00:42:40,400
He'll be with his
bodyguard and Stacie.

