678
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:50,300
Right, get yourselves in position.

679
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,200
Good luck.

680
00:42:52,900 --> 00:42:54,000
All right?

681
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:58,400
- Nice one.
- Take care, Albert.

682
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,200
So, Stacie called.

683
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:04,900
The money's in the trading account
but when we get there,

684
00:43:04,900 --> 00:43:07,400
Wasem needs to put his pin number in,
before we can move it.

685
00:43:07,500 --> 00:43:08,500
OK.

686
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:11,500
We'll clear out of the penthouse and
meet at the hotel when it's done.

687
00:43:11,700 --> 00:43:14,600
We'll split the money by
direct transfer, and then...

688
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,900
all go our separate ways.

689
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:24,600
- Everyone know what they're doing?
- Right.

690
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:29,400
What about me?

691
00:43:29,500 --> 00:43:30,500
Eh?

692
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:32,800
Everyone's talking about
the biggest job ever,

693
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:36,600
you know, history in the making and all that
and everyone's got something to do except me.

694
00:43:37,900 --> 00:43:39,600
Even the bloody dogs
have got a part.

695
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:44,700
Yeah, yeah, well, er, there's a reason
we haven't given you anything yet, Ed.

696
00:43:45,100 --> 00:43:49,100
- Yeah?
- Because we've saved the best till last.

697
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:53,200
Ah, see, I thought it'd be
something like that.

698
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:56,200
So, what? Do I get like
a uniform, an' all that?

699
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:57,800
No, you won't need one,

700
00:43:58,300 --> 00:44:02,300
you see, the most important
part of your job...

701
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:08,100
is to have the drinks ready and on
the table for when we get back.

702
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:14,100
Good luck, Ed.

703
00:44:40,500 --> 00:44:42,100
Sir, we need your pin.

704
00:44:47,700 --> 00:44:49,100
Thank you.

705
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:55,200
OK.
Three minutes.

706
00:44:57,700 --> 00:45:01,200
- That it?
- Yeah. Like we were never here.

707
00:45:20,800 --> 00:45:22,500
What's happening with my money?

708
00:45:24,300 --> 00:45:25,600
It's all right.

709
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:27,100
It's buying.

710
00:46:06,800 --> 00:46:08,800
Are we ready to do the transfer?

711
00:46:10,200 --> 00:46:15,800
So, now, we transferring his ten million
from the trading account, into our account.

712
00:46:24,600 --> 00:46:25,700
- Hi.
- Hello.

713
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:28,900
- We have a reservation,
under the name of Jones.
- OK.

714
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:58,400
This is the most fun I've ever had.
You know what?

715
00:46:58,500 --> 00:47:01,400
I think we come back tomorrow,
we do it all over again.

716
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:06,500
Stay where you are!
Get on the floor! Down now!

717
00:47:06,800 --> 00:47:09,400
Armed Police! Nobody move!

718
00:47:09,500 --> 00:47:12,500
You are under arrest on suspicion of fraud.

719
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:19,800
Come on.
Come on.

720
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:22,700
- This has nothing to do with us.
- All right, darlin', tell it to the judge.

721
00:47:22,700 --> 00:47:24,600
No, no, no, I mean it.

722
00:47:24,700 --> 00:47:27,700
They did it, they have this machine,
they wanted us to invest.

723
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:29,200
That's what happened,
she's telling the truth!

724
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:31,900
- We didn't even give them the money.
- Hold up.

725
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:36,000
Bring 'em back.

726
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,400
Take the rest of them away.

727
00:47:41,300 --> 00:47:43,500
It was...it was just
a demonstration,

728
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:45,700
we only met them yesterday.

729
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:49,500
They were trying to convince
us to invest but we didn't.

730
00:47:51,500 --> 00:47:54,000
Open the bag, you can
see for yourself.

731
00:48:00,400 --> 00:48:02,500
- So, this is your money?
- Yes.

732
00:48:03,700 --> 00:48:08,000
B-But it doesn't have to be.
It could be yours.

733
00:48:08,100 --> 00:48:11,000
So, if it just disappeared.

734
00:48:12,400 --> 00:48:16,900
There is half a million pounds
in cash in that bag, so...

735
00:48:19,300 --> 00:48:22,800
If you let us go we won't
even look back, I swear.

736
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:26,800
I've got a jet fuelled
and ready to leave,

