00:48:27,100 --> 00:48:30,000
I can be out of the
country in an hour.

738
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:34,600
You've got the machine,
the people who built it.

739
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:36,900
Why do you need us?

740
00:48:49,700 --> 00:48:51,600
Our friend's on his
way to the airport.

741
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:54,100
Stacie's going to lose him and
meet you back at the hotel.

742
00:48:54,800 --> 00:48:56,700
You son of a bitch, you did it.

743
00:48:56,700 --> 00:48:58,200
Hold tight.

744
00:49:11,300 --> 00:49:12,300
You did well.

745
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:15,000
Just get on the plane before
they change their mind.

746
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:37,500
We're back.

747
00:49:37,500 --> 00:49:41,500
- Ah. Hey.
- Ha-ha-ha.

748
00:49:43,500 --> 00:49:47,000
Current balance, ten million pounds.

749
00:49:47,200 --> 00:49:50,700
- Yes!
- And he gave us half a mill commission
in cash for taking it off him.

750
00:49:50,700 --> 00:49:52,600
Yeah-hey.

751
00:49:52,700 --> 00:49:54,400
???

752
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:56,300
Thank you, my dear.

753
00:49:57,900 --> 00:50:01,500
- To us. To us!
- Yeah, yeah! Woo hoo!

754
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:07,700
They've just gone into the hotel.
No. No police.

755
00:50:18,300 --> 00:50:20,700
- Ah, taste of victory.
- Scary. Scary.

756
00:50:22,400 --> 00:50:24,300
Guys, get out.

757
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:27,900
Go. Go, go, move.

758
00:50:31,900 --> 00:50:33,300
Come on, Albert.

759
00:51:15,100 --> 00:51:16,300
Mickey Bricks,

760
00:51:17,100 --> 00:51:19,700
if you've ever been brilliant,
please be brilliant now.

761
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:47,100
Gentlemen. I know what
you're thinking but, er...

762
00:52:36,300 --> 00:52:40,200
That's my money. That's my money.
Come on, come on.

763
00:53:01,700 --> 00:53:05,700
I guess most of you
must have thought that,

764
00:53:06,300 --> 00:53:09,000
one day, it would end like this.

765
00:53:14,100 --> 00:53:18,300
Which, without an extraordinary
amount of planning,

766
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:20,700
it very well might have done.

767
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:28,500
Come on, then. Off your arses.
Wakey wakey.

768
00:53:28,500 --> 00:53:30,600
Honestly, eh?

769
00:53:30,700 --> 00:53:34,600
What would you lot do without me coming
to bale you out of trouble all the time?

770
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:36,500
I mean it's all right Mickey
doing all that,

771
00:53:36,500 --> 00:53:39,900
"Look at me, I'm a clever bastard"
stuff, but when it comes down to it.

772
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:42,400
You just can't do it
without me, can you?

773
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:44,900
- Are you sure you couldn't find anyone else?
- I'm sorry.

774
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:49,200
Hello. Who's this? Very pretty.
Hello, sweetheart.

775
00:53:49,500 --> 00:53:52,800
I'm Danny. Danny Blue.
Probably heard a lot about me.

776
00:53:56,500 --> 00:53:58,800
Call my enforcer,
get him on a plane.

777
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:23,000
- Alex Klukas?
- I'm here.

778
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:26,300
Hello, Mickey.

779
00:54:29,300 --> 00:54:30,500
Try this on.

780
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:35,700
Just for the record, this isn't an
accurate representation of my underwear.

781
00:54:47,500 --> 00:54:50,500
I want you to learn how
they programme the machine.

782
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:54,500
How does the machine work?

783
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:57,300
Well, basically, it's a box
with a bunch of lights in it.

784
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:00,000
I thought it might be.

785
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:03,000
Gentlemen.
I know what you're thinking.

786
00:55:12,300 --> 00:55:14,800
Come on then, off your arses.

787
00:55:16,100 --> 00:55:20,400
- Did you, er, did you throw it all over?
- Nah, fifty grand or so.

788
00:55:42,500 --> 00:55:44,500
Er, now might be a good
time to slip away.

789
00:55:44,500 --> 00:55:46,200
I think that's a fabulous idea.

790
00:55:46,800 --> 00:55:49,700
How about, me and you, we
just slip away together?

791
00:55:49,800 --> 00:55:51,100
Danny, behave.

792
00:55:51,100 --> 00:55:52,200
Easy pal, that's my sister.

793
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:54,500
Whoa, everybody's a bit
touchy, ain't they?

794
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,700
I didn't have to use blanks,
you know, I did think about it.

795
00:55:58,400 --> 00:56:00,700
- How you doing, Albie?
- Pretty good, Danny, pretty good.

796
00:56:00,900 --> 00:56:03,700
- I'm sorry I had to shoot you.
- Don't worry about it.

797
00:56:03,700 --> 00:56:05,200
I blame Mickey.
He's very theatrical.

798
00:56:05,200 --> 00:56:08,600
- Someone shut him up.
- It was OTT, that's all I'm saying.

799
00:56:08,600 --> 00:56:10,900
- We were still being watched. 
- Exactly.

800
00:56:10,900 --> 00:56:12,200
Always playing to the audience.

801
00:56:12,200 --> 00:56:14,500
Listen, listen, mate, when you've
taken someone for ten million,

802
00:56:14,500 --> 00:56:17,500
the only way you can be sure they're not
coming after you is if they think you're dead.

803
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:19,400
Ten million?

804
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:22,100
Is this a good time
to talk about my cut?

805
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:23,400
I think we'd better be going.

806
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:25,600
Time we should make a move, come on.

807
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:32,800
Wahey. Yeah.

808
00:56:33,500 --> 00:56:36,600
- I've just had an amazing and original idea.
- God, help us.

809
00:56:36,600 --> 00:56:40,400
Bear with me, right, one, two,
three, there's seven of us, right?

810
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:44,200
We should hook up. We'll start
a new gang,

811
00:56:44,600 --> 00:56:47,200
maybe I'll lead it, we'll call it....

812
00:56:47,700 --> 00:56:49,300
The Magnificent Seven.

813
00:56:50,800 --> 00:56:52,200
What d'you think, Albert?

814
00:56:52,500 --> 00:56:55,200
I think that's a hell of an idea.

815
00:56:56,000 --> 00:57:00,000
- What about The Great Eight?
- To The Great Eight.

816
00:57:02,100 --> 00:57:04,300
So, that's it.
I'm out of here.

817
00:57:04,800 --> 00:57:07,100
I hope you've picked up
a few things along the way.

818
00:57:07,700 --> 00:57:11,200
If something seems too good to
be true, it almost certainly is.

819
00:57:11,600 --> 00:57:13,100
Always look a gift horse in the mouth.

820
00:57:13,100 --> 00:57:15,400
Unless you don't much care
whether it has teeth or not.

821
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:18,800
And, remember, you can't
cheat an honest man.

822
00:57:19,500 --> 00:57:22,200
So, if you bend the rules
to make some easy money,

823
00:57:22,300 --> 00:57:23,500
you deserve what you get.

824
00:57:24,400 --> 00:57:27,400
Oh, and, er, don't believe
everything people tell you.

825
00:57:28,300 --> 00:57:29,700
Whoever they are.

826
00:57:31,100 --> 00:57:33,200
Think things through for yourself.

827
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:35,700
Is it for real?

828
00:57:36,700 --> 00:57:40,000
Is someone telling you
that story for a reason?

829
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:46,000
Or...are they
having you right at it?

830
00:57:48,700 --> 00:57:50,000
But most important of all...

831
00:57:50,000 --> 00:57:51,100
Whether it's business...

832
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:52,900
- Buying.
- Selling.

833
00:57:53,100 --> 00:57:56,500
- Whether it's someone you know.
- Or someone you don't.

834
00:57:56,700 --> 00:57:59,000
Even if it's love.

835
00:58:03,200 --> 00:58:05,000
Never be a mark.

